caption1_text: More important however is what I learned about myself.
caption2_text: First you must gain their trust.
caption3_text: Well it was just easier than making a thousand tiny lab coats.

caption1_text: This is my stop. Phil you'll be C.E.O. till Sixty-third Street.
caption2_text: Yes I do miss the corporate jet. I miss the corporate jet very much.
caption3_text: Frank called to say he'll be late—he's stuck at the office.

caption1_text: Neither the time nor the place Doug!
caption2_text: Would it kill you to use a few of your roaming minutes?
caption3_text: This better be good. That floor was waxed last night!

caption1_text: Remember that time you made me laugh and people came out of my nose?
caption2_text: How about Little Italy for dessert?
caption3_text: Pass me a beer truck.

caption1_text: Tell my one-thirty things got way gnarly.
caption2_text: Gotta reschedule. Water-main break on Seventh!
caption3_text: Hold my calls cancel my appointments and find my Speedo!

caption1_text: It's me '9' from yoga class.
caption2_text: Last thing I remember the guy said ‘Pick a number.’
caption3_text: I represent several Arabic numerals who are being held without charges.

caption1_text: Relax honey—everybody gets buyer's remorse.
caption2_text: You always get like this when there's a full earth.
caption3_text: It's just the wind.

caption1_text: He's the cutest little thing and when you get tired of him you just flush him down the toilet.
caption2_text: You wouldn't believe it! I met a man at the pet store.
caption3_text: We decided on separate vacations this year.

caption1_text: Try telling that to the Kansas Board of Education.
caption2_text: What's more important youthful hair or F.D.A. approval?
caption3_text: Simple. I just wear my pants backward.

caption1_text: Well if you must know he makes me laugh.
caption2_text: I'm beginning to think I liked you better when you worked at Morgan Stanley.
caption3_text: I told you not to bring the clown!

caption1_text: I guess my wife couldn't make it.
caption2_text: Frankly your brochure is a bit misleading.
caption3_text: Gee you guys really are having trouble meeting your recruitment quota.

caption1_text: And tomorrow I'll teach you how to build a nest.
caption2_text: Can I have your apartment?
caption3_text: There's a message on my leg from Karl Rove.

caption1_text: This is why I love yard sales.
caption2_text: O.K. Now you be the naughty mosquito and I'll be the tormented sporting-goods salesman.
caption3_text: I think we need a new sex therapist.

caption1_text: Oh sure they find one secretary in a pool of her own blood and everybody wants to blame the werewolf.
caption2_text: Four hundred grand in damages? It was made out of straw for Chrissake!
caption3_text: Yes of course I've tried waxing.

caption1_text: Well it's a lovely gesture but I still think we should start seeing other people.
caption2_text: Don't move. I think I have something in my teeth.
caption3_text: It may look like the Virgin Mary but I don't see how you can sell it on eBay.

caption1_text: O.K. they're yours but I still don't know where you got that fourth ace.
caption2_text: Keep your eye out for a blond kid with a laser pointer.
caption3_text: I think it's important for them to hear both sides of the debate.

caption1_text: Yes I tried tapping on the glass.
caption2_text: Well the good news is the giant worms are gone.
caption3_text: Maybe you'll believe me once I've been regurgitated.

caption1_text: FEMA here. No we haven't had any substantiated reports of earthquakes.
caption2_text: Let me call you back. I left God holding on the other line.
caption3_text: Miss Jones send in the extra paperweights.

caption1_text: 'See Spot run.' 'See Spot run'? Who wrote this crap?
caption2_text: You won't believe this but I just remembered where I buried the remote.
caption3_text: Oh did I mention that Timmy fell down the well?

caption1_text: We met at the minibar.
caption2_text: Larry can't tell you about his current project—it's top secret.
caption3_text: Whatever you do don't agree to play hide-and-seek with him.

caption1_text: This is why I always dress in bright colors.
caption2_text: It's our new interactive TV. When he's done I'm having an appendectomy on 'General Hospital.'
caption3_text: We've got a thirty-six-inch plasma mounted in the den.

caption1_text: Well then it's unanimous.
caption2_text: Who else found Gary's report a little too angry white and male?
caption3_text: So that settles it. This year instead of cooking the books we'll bake them in a light flaky pastry.

caption1_text: But how will we raise the kids?
caption2_text: You think this is weird? My sister looks like a soup can.
caption3_text: It's not traditional but I find it attracts a more mature type of female.

caption1_text: Hold my hand and we can use the car-pool lane.
caption2_text: I had another one of those walking dreams last night.
caption3_text: Can you believe the fairy-dust prices these days?

caption1_text: Bob just came directly from work.
caption2_text: We don't have much of a sex life but he's good at finding keys in the swimming pool.
caption3_text: This suit looked way better in the store.

caption1_text: That concludes tonight's performance of ‘Pimp My Ride of the Valkyries.'
caption2_text: This season we welcome a new corporate sponsor.
caption3_text: Sorry I'm late.

caption1_text: Shut up Bob everyone knows your parrot's a clip-on.
caption2_text: We have to find a better way to record our meetings.
caption3_text: Well it's not my fault booty revenues are down this quarter.

caption1_text: Dibs on the briefcase.
caption2_text: Uh-oh. That last village must have been incorporated.
caption3_text: There goes the neighborhood.

caption1_text: And in this section it appears that you have not only alienated voters but actually infected them too.
caption2_text: The inland tortellini are still with you sir but you're losing support with the coastal risottos.
caption3_text: Stay with me sir. It's almost recess.

caption1_text: Instead of an expensive invasive procedure we've decided to beat it out of you.
caption2_text: Good news! We have a solid lead on who stole your liver.
caption3_text: That rash will need constant monitoring.

caption1_text: If I'm not back at the maze by eight my wife reels in the damn string.
caption2_text: If they ask for Ted's Stud Service I'll take it.
caption3_text: Don't tell me it's halftime already.

caption1_text: It's not just Henderson. Corporate laid off the entire bunny division.
caption2_text: Well there he goes—the first casualty of the War on Easter.
caption3_text: Well at least somebody remembered about casual Good Friday.

caption1_text: So then I guess the Johnsons are feeding our clothes.
caption2_text: I never know what to pack.
caption3_text: I just thought of something. What if your parents don't collect dead goldfish anymore?

caption1_text: I bet the bride of Frankenstein gets to cuddle.
caption2_text: And where do you think you're going with those curtains?
caption3_text: I guess this rules out a church wedding.

caption1_text: To be fair Martha you started it.
caption2_text: Oh he probably just smells <u>your</u> python.
caption3_text: You see what happens when you carry rats in your purse?

caption1_text: No one expects an immaculate conception until it happens to him.
caption2_text: The ultrasound says it's a keg of Bud Light.
caption3_text: She told me she had protection.

caption1_text: Are you now or have you ever been?
caption2_text: The committee will ask you one final time: do you come in a 42?
caption3_text: He won't get far.

caption1_text: That's the last time we brag about our kids.
caption2_text: At the end of the day I guess I'm just really more of a cat person.
caption3_text: Sure she's cute but she'll never have a dancer's body.

caption1_text: They give me free drinks if I keep my tray table down.
caption2_text: I'm sure I've got a business card on me somewhere.
caption3_text: I only bring clothes that I definitely need.

caption1_text: Well that was abominable.
caption2_text: I just wish we could talk about something other than global warming.
caption3_text: I think the Manhattan skyline is getting suspicious.

caption1_text: Finally—a faith-based initiative I can embrace.
caption2_text: Just don't order a Bloody Mary.
caption3_text: Hey! Who ya gotta pray to to get a drink around here?

caption1_text: Cancel my twelve-oh-one.
caption2_text: I can't talk I'm expecting a call from the governor . . . wait I could save how much?
caption3_text: Yes Mother I know I should have started my appeal earlier.

caption1_text: How many surprise witnesses do you have in that little car?
caption2_text: Ooh ... I'm going to allow <u>this</u>!
caption3_text: I don't know about you counsellor but I kind of wish there were more murders at the circus.

caption1_text: It's not good—looks like they've got a full interpretive-dance troupe.
caption2_text: O.K. send him in. But this goes against the Geneva conventions.
caption3_text: Not a good day for a street fair.

caption1_text: Back in my day kids had a little respect for the law of gravity.
caption2_text: Unfortunately at this age they don't carry much pocket change.
caption3_text: I told you those humane traps never really work.

caption1_text: First I'd like to thank the podium.
caption2_text: Do I hear a motion for less disclosure?
caption3_text: If all goes well we'll get them back after the audit.

caption1_text: How soon can you start?
caption2_text: Our conflict-resolution seminar ended a bit early today.
caption3_text: Just remember to keep away from Fletcher's wife and Davidson's daughter and Harris's iPod.

caption1_text: O.K. this time with a little less feeling.
caption2_text: Gosh Wendy that was more like 'The Flight of the Whole Hive.'
caption3_text: Yes dear I'm sure your grandmother can hear you in Heaven.

caption1_text: Stop me if you've heard this one.
caption2_text: I thought I told you to stop sending me jokes at work.
caption3_text: It's gonna be one of those long nights of playing devil's advocate.

caption1_text: But what if you fall when no one is around?
caption2_text: I'd divorce you but we need the firewood.
caption3_text: How’s your new boss at the C.I.A. dear?
